summary:
A 4-year-old living in an area with only 0.2 ppm fluoride should receive safe, targeted prevention through supervised use of fluoride toothpaste (like 1,000 ppm). Systemic supplements exceed recommended doses or pose undue fluorosis risk, while topical treatments such as rinses or gels are unsafe or impractical for young children due to inhalation/aspiration hazards.  

\boxed{D} 

